<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_ævgærdæn" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
    <form type="lemma"><orth>ævgærdæn</orth></form>
    <sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>шея</q>
        </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>neck</q>
        </cit></sense>
    <re xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/><form type="lemma"><orth>bærzæj</orth></form></re>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Причастное образование на -%iæn%i от глагола %iævgærd%i-%iun%i (и. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_ærgævdyn"/>) ‘резать’, ‘закалывать’: „место, которое режут (у
        животного)“ → ‘шея’. Для развития значения ср. <mentioned xml:lang="uby"
                ><lang/><w>pik-faki-ϕä</w><gloss><q>горло</q></gloss></mentioned>, буквально
        „шея-место-резания“ (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Mészaros"
        /><biblScope>252</biblScope></bibl>Mészaros 252), <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><lang/><w>зарез</w><gloss><q>часть шеи</q></gloss></mentioned> (у животного); ср.
        также <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>boǧaz</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"
                >—</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"
            >—</note><gloss><q>горло</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w>boǧozla</w><gloss><q>заколоть</q></gloss></mentioned>, %bгур.%b (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>IV 1650</biblScope></bibl>). К <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>gardan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>γrδk</w><gloss><q>шея</q></gloss></mentioned> дигорское слово,
                вопреки<bibl><author>А. Фрейману </author><biblScope>(Rocznik Orient. 3, 1926, стр.
                162)</biblScope></bibl>, никакого отношения не имеет: начальному иранскому %ig%i не
        может отвечать осетинское %ig%i. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærgævdyn"
        />ærgævdyn.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">A participle form derived with the suffix -%iæn%i from the verb
        %iævgærd%i-%iun%i (Iron <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærgævdyn"/>) ‘to cut’, ‘to slaughter’:
        „a spot to cut (on an animal)“ → ‘neck’. For the development of the meaning cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="uby"><lang/><w>pik-faki-ϕä</w><gloss><q>throat</q></gloss></mentioned>,
        literally „neck-spot-cutting“ (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Mészaros"
            /><biblScope>252</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                    ><lang/><w>zarez</w><gloss><q>a part of neck</q></gloss></mentioned> (of
        animal); cf. also <mentioned xml:lang="hac"><lang/><w>boǧaz</w><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="ru">—</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"
                    >—</note><gloss><q>throat</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="hac"
                ><w>boǧozla</w><gloss><q>to slaughter</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>IV 1650</biblScope></bibl>). Unlike A. Freiman's
        hypothesis (<bibl><author>A. Freiman</author><biblScope>Rocznik Orient. 3, 1926, p.
                162</biblScope></bibl>), the Digor word does not relate to <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>gardan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                    ><lang/><w>γrδk</w><gloss><q>neck</q></gloss></mentioned>: The Ossetic %ig%i
        cannot relate to the initial Iranian %ig%i. See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærgævdyn"
        />.</etym>
</entry>
